                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/872: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-20T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1919, 12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 8.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s September 18, 4 p.m.<note n="43" xml:id="d298fn43">“Cable Department
                        whether protocol has been signed and when McIlhenny will leave.”</note> Full
                    powers not yet received. McIlhenny will leave immediately after signature
                    protocol.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
